  "description": "Hematocrit (Hct) is the volume percentage of red blood cells in whole blood. It is a measure of red blood cell mass and oxygen-carrying capacity of the blood. Normal ranges vary by age, sex, and other factors such as altitude and pregnancy status.",
  "clinical_use": "Used to diagnose and monitor anemia, polycythemia (erythrocytosis), dehydration, and response to treatments such as transfusion. Also guides therapeutic phlebotomy in polycythemia vera.",
